    "about" : "<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>OUR MISSION</strong></p>\n\n<p>Rural Women Empowerment and Youth development Foundation [RWEYDF];&nbsp;We have a mandate to create opportunities and enabling environment for Women and Youths in the rural areas to harness their potentials and channel this towards personal and societal development.</p>\n\n<p><strong>OUR VISION</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Working towards a caring societyWorking towards a caring society</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>OUR AIMS AND OBJECTIVES</strong></p>\n\n<p>It is in consonance with the highlighted mission and vision above that the foundation intends to accelerate the process of development through the following:</p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>&nbsp;traditional textile promotion as an area to create employement and empowerment [promotion of popular Ebira Woven Cloths of Tie and Dye]</li>\n\t<li>educational promotion and socio-cultural enlightenment</li>\n\t<li>scholarship awards to indigent students in both post-primary and tertiary institutions through the organized National Youth Council of Nigerian [NYCN] Kogi State Chapter-Youths are the trustees of prosperitry.</li>\n\t<li>enlightening and re-orientating the public some prevailing killer diseases such as HIV/Aids, malaria, tuberculous etc.</li>\n\t<li>enligthenement campaign through regular interactions wih stakeholders for a sustainable sensitization and mobilization in order to achieve acceptable social conduct and equitable participation in all spheres of developmemt.</li>\n\t<li>the foundation shall also visit and support orphans, motherless baby homes and less priviledged and aged persons.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>OUR MISSION</strong></p>\n\n<p>Rural Women Empowerment and Youth development Foundation [RWEYDF];&nbsp;We have a mandate to create opportunities and enabling environment for Women and Youths in the rural areas to harness their potentials and channel this towards personal and societal development.</p>\n\n<p><strong>OUR VISION</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Working towards a caring societyWorking towards a caring society</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>OUR AIMS AND OBJECTIVES</strong></p>\n\n<p>It is in consonance with the highlighted mission and vision above that the foundation intends to accelerate the process of development through the following:</p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>&nbsp;traditional textile promotion as an area to create employement and empowerment [promotion of popular Ebira Woven Cloths of Tie and Dye]</li>\n\t<li>educational promotion and socio-cultural enlightenment</li>\n\t<li>scholarship awards to indigent students in both post-primary and tertiary institutions through the organized National Youth Council of Nigerian [NYCN] Kogi State Chapter-Youths are the trustees of prosperitry.</li>\n\t<li>enlightening and re-orientating the public some prevailing killer diseases such as HIV/Aids, malaria, tuberculous etc.</li>\n\t<li>enligthenement campaign through regular interactions wih stakeholders for a sustainable sensitization and mobilization in order to achieve acceptable social conduct and equitable participation in all spheres of developmemt.</li>\n\t<li>the foundation shall also visit and support orphans, motherless baby homes and less priviledged and aged persons.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>CORE VALUES</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Integrity</li>\n\t<li>Accountability</li>\n\t<li>Transparency</li>\n\t<li>Gender equity</li>\n\t<li>Team Work</li>\n\t<li>Leadership</li>\n\t<li>Human Rights</li>\n\t<li>Education (Bedrock of any progressive society)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>GOALS</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Introduction and Sustenance of a Youth Educational Scheme to provide Scholarship and others Educational assistance</li>\n\t<li>Development of new systems and modification of existing structures to incorporate gender and human rights issues and mechanisms</li>\n\t<li>To create awareness in the public on health issues such as HIV and Malaria and provide systems for access to affordable and effective health care</li>\n\t<li>To help rural communities to develop and maintain a Micro-Credit Scheme for rural market women and proffer ways for access to capital with training on financial and managerial skills</li>\n\t<li>To create grounds for children to express themselves and development of positive leadership and skills</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>To provide forums for community discussions as a research tool for NEEDS assessment to provide data for policy makers.</p>\n\n<p><strong>STRATEGIES</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Advocacy/Public Walks</li>\n\t<li>Focus Group Discussions.</li>\n\t<li>Peaceful co-existence, Health wing, Micro-credit and Educational upliftment.</li>\n\t<li>Leadership Training.</li>\n\t<li>Educational Strategy (Scholarship/Lifting Orphans to School/Empowerment)</li>\n\t<li>In school seminars</li>\n\t<li>Community health talks/Assistance</li>\n\t<li>Community mobilization</li>\n\t<li>Train the Trainers programs</li>\n\t<li>Income generating activities</li>\n\t<li>Staff &nbsp;Development</li>\n\t<li>Networking and Partnership with other NGOs</li>\n\t<li>Empowerment through Skill acquisitions.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n",
